editorialNotes.standard: Bursting with beats and energy, Toca Dance will make the whole family want to get up and groove. This incredibly cute game puts kids in charge of their own musical productionâchoosing dancers, costumes, and techno tracks, and choreographing moves using simple swipes and taps. Once the performance starts, the real fun begins: you can fling items at the stage, set off pyrotechnics and other cool effects, and even cheer (or boo) your squad. Seeing the payoffâan awesome video you can shareâwill encourage players to jump right back in and start working on their next great show.

Learning the ABCs is child's play with this entertaining and educational app. Adorable artwork, colorful creatures, and smooth voice and sound effects enhance an already engaging hands-on experience that makes spelling each and every word an interactive puzzle.

Nothing beats a kid-friendly game that keeps the whole family captivatedâand Toca has us snipping, straightening, and styling to our heart's content. Once we've perfected our customer's silly new âdos, we make sure to add some accessories, snap a pic, and share the hair.

The moment we met wee kitty Crumbs in Little Kitten, we let out an audible âawww.â This adorable digital feline encourages children to play and explore, interacting with the lively toys and simple games in Crumbsâ room. Weâre amazed by the cinematic animation, and appreciate the sleep timer that sends Crumbs to bed when our kidsâ screen time is over.
editorialNotes.short: Embark on exciting adventures with your own kitty pal.

editorialNotes.standard: Slide a shape into the correct holeâeasy, right? It is, at first. But what makes Busy Shapes so clever is the way it gently gets more challenging, motivating little kids to find solutions to each puzzle through experimentation. From shape-changing to color-mixing to hidden holes, weâre impressed with how the gameplay spurs out-of-the-box thinking, stimulating curious young minds.

editorialNotes.standard: This charming bedtime story will soothe your young child with delightful imagery and a simple but engaging spoken tale. Inside an exquisitely illustrated farmhouse, adorable woodland animals need help turning out the lights to fall asleep. Intuitive controls and fun interactive surprises make Nighty Night a pleasure to explore, and with optional narration, you and your toddler can settle in to be entertained or bring your own imaginations to the wonderful nighttime world.

See the beauty and power of ABCs in an app where every letter holds secret words. Touch an F, and it sprouts a foot, then feathers, then a fan; a G becomes a guitar in a garden with ghosts. Kids will love poking and prodding their way to the end of the alphabet, while parents will dig the unpredictability and gorgeous animation in this Apple Design Award winner.
editorialNotes.short: Interactive alphabet learning where words and letters come to life.

editorialNotes.standard: An utterly charming way to introduce young kids to music and animation, Loopimal is simple and powerful in a way that almost defies description. Kids arrange and rearrange tiles in sequences underneath a cute polar bear, octopus, and the like, triggering a series of musical tones mirrored by adorable dances from the animal gang. There are no goals and no consequencesâjust a safe place to learn, play, and laugh.

Part digital toy and part planetary handbook, The Earth gives kids insight into the workings of our world in a way thatâs delightfully intuitive and fun. From rockslides to earthquakes to erupting volcanoes, these artful interactive dioramas respond to tapping and swiping with results that are both whimsical and educational. An accompanying guide for parents and teachers delves into the technical science behind all these phenomena, but kids can explore, experiment, and absorb earthly knowledge at their own pace.
editorialNotes.short: Play with interactive models to understand our planet.
